  <shortlink>api isdigit function</shortlink>
   <topic>ISDIGIT Function</topic>
   <description>Returns TRUE if the first character of a string is a digit.</description>
 
   <syntax>Result_Flag as L = ISDIGIT(C character)</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>character</name>
         <description>A character string.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>  <discussion>
ISDIGIT() returns .T. (TRUE) if the first character of Character_String is a number; otherwise, it returns .F. (FALSE).

   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[? isdigit("Alpha")
= .F.
? isdigit("1Alpha")
= .T.]]></example>
   
   <see>
      <ref link="Type Checking Functions">Type Checking Functions</ref>
   </see>
  
